{{unreferenced|date=March 2013}} {{Infobox military conflict |partof=the [[First Indochina War]] |place=[[Nghia Lo]], [[Vietnam]] |date=3–10 October 1951 |result=French victory |combatant1={{Flagicon|North Vietnam|1945}} [[Viet Minh]] |combatant2={{flag|France}} |commander1=[[Lê Trọng Tấn]] |commander2=[[Rémy Raffalli]] |strength1=2,400 |strength2=450 |casualties1=300 killed |casualties2=60 killed }} {{Campaignbox First Indochina War}} The '''Battle of Nghia Lo''' (Vietnamese: '''Nghĩa Lộ'''), was fought between the [[French army]] and the [[Viet Minh]] during the [[First Indochina War]]. On 3 October, the Viet Minh [[312th Division (Vietnam)|312th Division]] launched an attack on French forces in the town of Nghia Lo and its vicinity. The attack was repelled, after a week of fighting. A year later on 17 October, the Viet Minh launched another attack on Nghia Lo and suceceded in driving out the remaining French from the area.
